  <title>pressure</title>
  <index>quantity</index>
  <termversion>2.3.3</termversion>
  <lastupdated>2014-02-24</lastupdated>
  <definitions>
    <item>
      <id>1</id>
      <text>Normal force acting on a surface divided by the area of that surface. For a mixture of gases the contribution by each constituent is called the partial pressurep i = x i p, where x i is the amount fraction of the ith constituent and p is the total pressure.</text>
